President Joe Biden has declared a state of emergency in Guam due to the conditions caused by Tropical Storm Bolaven. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected population. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Under the Public Assistance program, 75 percent of funding for emergency protective measures will be provided by the federal government. Benigno B. Ruiz has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.